Controversial actor Uche Maduagwu has claimed he was paid to slander Davido for not getting married to his ‘sister’ Chioma Rowland. For a while, Davido and his estranged fiancée, Chioma were an item that he even made a song titled “Assurance” for her in 2018. Visuals of the song also featured the Chioma with whom he shares a son, Ifeanyi Adeleke, with the theme of the song centred on the fact that the singer vowed to always love her. The duo got engaged in 2019 and was supposed to tie the nuptial knot in 2020 but that didn’t happen. Rumours of their breakup was on the lips of many and was further fuelled after several intimate pictures of a singer and a 22-year-old American Instagram model, Mya Yafai, hit the internet in 2021.   What I find rude in men, by Tolani Baj     Nigeria in dire need of overhauling – Comedian AY     Ex-BBN Tacha, Mercy Ike reconcile   In one of the pictures, the “Fem” singer was seen giving Yafai a French kiss. Maduagwu, as well as other online in-laws of Chioma after Davido’s failure to marry her seized every opportunity to backlash him. Although, many still hoped the duo would one day come back together especially as Chioma was flown into London with her son in Davido’s private jet to attend his sold-out O2 arena concert in London earlier this month. But all hopes of their reunion seemed to have crashed following the disclosure of Chioma’s alleged new lover by a blogger who also shared his photo. However, Maduagwu has now made a u-turn as he sought the singer’s forgiveness over his incessant attacks. In an Instagram post, the media sensation wrote: “I was paid to criticise David for not getting married to my sis. Dear men, marriage no be by force. Biko forgive me. OBO you are more useful to us than audio Odogwu arrogance.”